UNDIAGNOSED ILLNESS, CAPRINE - KENYA
************************************
ProMED-mail, a Program of ISID
<http://www.promedmail.org>
Date: 19 Oct 2000
From: M. Cosgriff <mcosgriff@hotmail.com>
Source: East African Standard, 10 Oct 2000 [edited]

Rift Valley Province: Undiagnosed disease kills goats
-----------------------------------------------------
Hundreds of goats have died in Keiyo District following an outbreak of a
strange disease in the area.
According to livestock farmers led by the local county council chairman,
Mr Julius Chepkiyeng, the disease kills the animals within 10 hours of
infection [presumed to mean within 10 hours of exhibiting symptoms. - Mod.ES]
"Infected goats cough uncontrollably before succumbing to the disease
within 10 hours," Chepkiyeng said in Iten town.
The area deputy District Veterinary Officer, Dr Richard Kirui, confirmed
the outbreak of the disease and described its effects as devastating.
"We have carried out preliminary tests and established the disease is
linked to the contagious caprine pleuropneumonia. However, more tests
are to be carried out," he said.
